    "eldora": {
      "status": "ok",
      "resort": "Eldora",
      "adapter": "powdr",
      "updatedAt": "2026-03-09 05:34:15",
      "note": "5:42 AM update – Good morning, skiers and riders! Welcome to the Eldora snow report for Monday, March 9th, 2026. Happy Monday, everyone! With 19” of snow over the past week, the mountain is 97% open and it is looking absolutely incredible! Thanks to everyone who came out for Subaru Winter Fest this past weekend, let’s keep those good vibes going into the this week! With temps in the low 40s and sunny skies, it will another great warm weather day. Steady breezes with higher gusts will still bring out that winter feel so make sure to layer appropriately! Come up and enjoy the new snow while it lasts. Can’t wait to see you out there and let’s have a great week! Stay in the loop: This page, eldora.com/conditions , is always your go-to for the latest updates, but you can also sign up for text alerts so you never miss a beat. Text one of the following keywords to (866) 965-6224 for general alerts, text ELDORA, UPHILL for uphill-specific updates, or NORDIC for future Nordic updates. Message and data rates may apply. NWS Weather Snapshot: Patchy blowing snow before noon. Sunny, with a high near 41. Windy, with a west wind 24 to 31 mph, with gusts as high as 48 mph. Uphill, Nordic, and Snowshoe: Uphill access is open subject to the policies described at eldora.com/uphill . The Nordic Center is providing limited access for Nordic Season Pass Holders and Nordic 3-Pass guests; day-ticket access and snowshoeing are not yet available. Stay tuned to Nordic Pulse for the latest on the Nordic Center. Thanks for checking the Eldora snow report. We'll see you on the hill! -- GENERAL INFORMATION Lift Hours: 9:00 AM to 4:00 PM on weekdays, 8:30 AM to 4:00 PM on weekends. Lodge Hours: 8:00 AM to 4:30 PM on weekdays, 7:30 AM to 4:30 PM on weekends. Single-Occupancy Vehicle (SOV) Fees: Vehicles with two or more occupants may park for free seven days a week. Vehicles with one occupant will be charged $10 on weekends, during certain holiday periods, and on weekdays with 10 or more inches of new snow. Credit/debit is accepted; cash is not. High-Occupancy Vehicle (HOV) Parking: Per Boulder County requirements, the Elk Lot (nearest to Alpenglow chair) is reserved seven days a week for vehicles with three or more occupants on a first-come, first-served basis. Learn more here . EV Parking: Eldora provides 30 free ChargePoint EV charging stations. These premium parking spots are available on a first-come, first-served basis and are subject to the SOV policy above. To park in the EV lot, you MUST have an EV and be actively charging. If you are finished charging, please move your car to another non-EV space so others can use the chargers. Easy, Convenient RTD Bus Service from Boulder: RTD’s NB route brings you from Downtown Boulder Station straight to the Alpenglow chairlift in about 40 minutes; riders 19 and under ride RTD for FREE through RTD's Zero Fare for Youth program. For schedule and fare info, visit rtd-denver.com .",
